jit_vcr = MaxObject("jit.vcr")
"""
jit.vcr - Record a movie with MSP audio

Use the jit.vcr object combine a sequence of Jitter matrices and MSP audio and save the sequence to disk as a synchronized movie. The two left inlets accept MSP audio signals (if only 1 inlet is used, the movie's audio will be monophonic). The right inlet accepts a Jitter matrix.

Inlets:
  0 (INLET_TYPE): MSP audio in 1
  1 (INLET_TYPE): MSP audio in 2
  2 (matrix): in

Outlets:
  0 (matrix): out
  1 (matrix): dumpout

Messages: signal, stop, write

Attributes: adapt, codec, dstrect, engine, fps, interp, planemap, preview, srcrect, time, usedstrect, usesrcrect
"""

